The Arewa Consultative Forum (ACF) has called for calm following the dethronement of the Emir of Kano, Muhammad Sanusi II over what the Kano State Government described as “disrespect to lawful instructions from the State Governor and other lawful authorities.” The ACF in a statement issued by its National Publicity Secretary, Muhammad Ibrahim Biu on Monday stated that the Forum had earlier intervened in the feud between the Kano State Government and Kano Emirate Council and had called for amicable resolution. It stated that with Monday’s turn of event, the ACF calls for calm and understanding especially among the good people of Kano State and Nigerians. Malam Muhammadu Sanusi ll was dethroned over disrespect to the office of the governor and other government agencies. He was replaced by Alhaji Aminu Ado Bayero, the former emir of Bichi.  Mixed reactions trail Emir Sanusi’s dethronement Ganduje to name new Emir of Kano today Why we removed Sanusi as Emir of Kano — Ganduje